fscript-CLI 2.4 uses the PCRE files, but has XCode compile them directly into the tool, instead of using
the separate library file. Follow these steps to compile PCRE 8.39 into the fscript executable:

1. Unpack the pcre-8.39 archive, cd into the directory, and run these commands:
    ./configure --disable-cpp --enable-utf8
    make
    ./RunTest

2. Run the following commands to generate the default character tables:
    gcc -DHAVE_CONFIG_H -o dftables dftables.c
    ./dftables chartables.c
    
3. In Xcode, add -DSUPPORT_UTF8 and -DHAVE_CONFIG_H as compiler flags

4. Add the following files to the project:
    config.h
    pcre.h
    pcreposix.h
    pcre_internal.h
    pcre_scanner.h
    ucp.h
    chartables.c
    pcreposix.c
    pcre_compile.c
    pcre_config.c
    pcre_dfa_exec.c
    pcre_exec.c
    pcre_fullinfo.c
    pcre_get.c
    pcre_globals.c
    pcre_info.c
    pcre_maketables.c
    pcre_newline.c
    pcre_ord2utf8.c
    pcre_refcount.c
    pcre_study.c
    pcre_tables.c
    pcre_try_flipped.c
    pcre_ucd.c
    pcre_valid_utf8.c
    pcre_version.c
    pcre_xclass.c
    ucptable.c

5. In config.h, change the line '#define SUPPORT_UTF8' to '#define SUPPORT_UTF8 1'

